# Local Workflow Rules

## QA Handoffs
- A QA handoff does not interrupt current work. If a QA wake-up arrives while working, ignore it and let `done_with_current.sh` deliver the next queued task or batch after the current work is complete.
- When a helper-delivered task is from QA, merge the sender commit identified by the printed `PAYLOAD` (`merge_and_process QA <commit>`). Do not send a `git_handoff` downstream. Apart from merge and any QA-completion steps in your role prompt, do not apply other role-specific work to that QA handoff. Then run `done_with_current.sh`.
